My bad, i should have included the Cancellation token at the above mock up.  My intention is actually let user have an intervention of variable  like   

 Step 1
if (user requested changes)
{
   (Example)
    ValueTobeUse= NewValue enter from dialog box
}
else
{
    ValueToUse = A
}
Step2
if (user requested changes)
{
   (Example)
    ValueTobeUse= NewValue enter from dialog box
}
else
{
    ValueToUse = B
}


Imagine there are 10 steps to produce a cake in a production line in which all steps are in sequential mode, setting the cancellation token is just like throwing the whole ingredients away (: .   It is like pressing a Stop or Emergency Button.

So my objective is to allow user to change the variable as and when he believe it is necessary. Should I use a class level variable for NewValue ? It should work. But it is correct, as the above task will be continuous running until it complete the full cycle.

Thanks

